# GitHub Basics Guide

A beginner-friendly reference for using GitHub day to day.

---

## What Is GitHub?

**Git** is a version control system that tracks changes to your files over time.  
**GitHub** is a cloud-based platform that hosts Git repositories so you can collaborate, back up, and share your code.

---

## Key Concepts

| Term | What It Means |
|---|---|
| **Repository (Repo)** | A project folder tracked by Git |
| **Clone** | Download a copy of a repo to your machine |
| **Branch** | An isolated copy of the code to work in safely |
| **Commit** | A saved snapshot of your changes |
| **Push** | Upload your commits to GitHub |
| **Pull** | Download the latest changes from GitHub |
| **Pull Request (PR)** | A request to merge your branch into another branch |
| **Merge** | Combining one branch into another |
| **Fork** | Your own personal copy of someone else's repo |

