## The Basic Daily Workflow

This is the loop you will use every single day:

```
Pull → Make Changes → Stage → Commit → Push
```

### 1. Pull the latest changes first

```bash
git pull origin main
```

### 2. Make your changes
Edit your files in any editor.

### 3. Check what changed

```bash
git status
```

### 4. Stage your changes

```bash
# Stage a specific file
git add filename.txt

# Stage everything at once
git add .
```

### 5. Commit your changes

```bash
git commit -m "Brief description of what you changed"
```

> **Tip:** Write commit messages in plain English. Example: `"Fix login bug"` or `"Add README file"`

### 6. Push to GitHub

```bash
git push origin main
```

