## Common Issues & Fixes

### Merge Conflict
Happens when two people edited the same part of a file.

```bash
# After a failed merge, open the conflicted file and look for:
<<<<<<< HEAD
your changes
=======
their changes
>>>>>>> branch-name

# Edit the file to keep what you want, then:
git add filename.txt
git commit -m "Resolve merge conflict"
```

### Wrong Branch
```bash
# Stash your work, switch branches, then pop it back
git stash
git checkout correct-branch
git stash pop
```

### Forgot to Pull Before Working
```bash
git pull --rebase origin main
```

